reviews.headline: hear me out
reviews.comments: I purchased with my own money. I usually try to steer clear of products that seem over hyped by influencers, this being one of them. HOWEVER, I bought this bc I had recently tried out the LM tinted moisturizer - the matte one. I'm an oily gal. my previous base product was the HL foundation but that one wouldn't last on my t zone, even with setting, priming, etc. The LM made me extremely matte with the elf power grip. it lasted all day. BUT, I didn't want to look extremely dry. I bought this bc the niacinamide and serum ordeal called me. I was hoping it would give me some radiance without letting my oil pull through, especially on my forehead, and it did just that! I worked out and spent some time in the Texas sun. when I blotted, hardly ANYTHING was on my napkin. I looked glowy but it was this primer, not my actual oils! I will keep trying it out, but so far, this looks extremely promising and living up to the hype.

reviews.headline: New holy grail!
reviews.comments: I buy mostly prestige brands but was influenced by a tiktok routine to try this out. This feels nice going on, grippy. Not perfect but my makeup was all still there and my skin still looked nice. No sweat streaks, not cakey from wearing all day, didnt wash off in the rain. Amazing. This is making me question everything. 100% reccomend, its my new holy grail.

reviews.headline: Great and grippy!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I tested this primer for the first time this weekend, sticking to my usual skincare and makeup routine, and I was amazed by its effectiveness! I have combination skin, which often reacts poorly to new products, leading to breakouts or excess oil. However, this primer performed exceptionally well and truly lasted throughout the day; it also doesn't pill when applied over moisturizer. The texture felt like a sticky serum that dried down effectively, helping to reduce the appearance of oily skin as the day progressed. It really holds onto makeup, keeping it in place for hours. In addition to its performance, this primer also offers benefits like hydration and contains 2% niacinamide. I'm pleased to find that the formula is vegan and suitable for all skin types. It's wonderful to discover a product that works so effectively while remaining affordable and accessible. I highly recommend this primer if you're in the market for a new one! I received this product in exchange for my honest review.

reviews.headline: Great budget primer
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] 
I wasn't sure what to expect with the Maybelline Super Grippy Primer, but it totally earned its name. The texture is a little tacky when first applied (which threw me off at first), but that's exactly what makes it workâ€”it really grips your makeup and helps it stay in place all day. Foundation glides on smoothly over it and doesn't budge, even after hours of wear.

It's lightweight, doesn't clog pores, and gives my skin a slightly blurred, smoother look. I've tried it under both drugstore and higher-end foundations, and it plays well with everything. Oily skin? This helps with shine. Dry patches? It smooths over them without pilling.

Only reason I knocked off half a star is that the tacky feel isn't for everyone, and if you apply too much, it can feel a bit heavy. But overall, if you're looking for a budget-friendly primer that truly locks your makeup in, this one's a hidden gem. I didn't notice any strong scent.

Review of Maybelline Grippy Serum â€“ Makeup Grip Primer

The product in the image is Maybelline Grippy Serum, a makeup gripping primer infused with 2% niacinamide, promising up to 24-hour wear. Here's a detailed review:

Pros:

âœ” Grippy Texture for Long-Lasting Makeup â€“ The serum has a slightly sticky texture that helps foundation adhere better and last longer.
âœ” Hydrating Formula â€“ Contains 2% niacinamide, which helps smooth and brighten the skin while keeping it hydrated.
âœ” Lightweight & Fast-Absorbing â€“ It feels light on the skin, absorbs quickly, and doesn't leave a heavy or greasy residue.
âœ” Smooths Skin & Minimizes Pores â€“ Helps blur imperfections and create a smooth canvas for makeup.
âœ” Versatile for Different Skin Types â€“ Works well for normal, oily, and combination skin, though dry skin users might need additional moisturizer.

Cons:

âš  Sticky Finish Might Not Suit Everyone â€“ Since it has a tacky finish, some people may find it uncomfortable if they prefer a silky-smooth primer.
âš  Not Mattifying â€“ While it helps makeup stay in place, it doesn't control oil, so those with very oily skin might need additional setting products.
âš  Limited Skincare Benefits â€“ Though it contains niacinamide, it's primarily a primer, not a full skincare serum, so results for brightening or acne control may be minimal.

Who Should Try It?

Those who want a long-lasting base for makeup â€“ If your foundation tends to fade throughout the day, this can help extend its wear.

People looking for a primer with skincare benefits â€“ The niacinamide infusion is a plus for brightening and smoothing skin.

Best for normal to oily skin types â€“ Dry skin users may need extra hydration before applying this primer.

Final Verdict:

ðŸ‘‰ If you're looking for a hydrating, grippy primer that extends makeup wear, Maybelline Grippy Serum is a great choice. However, if you prefer a matte or silky primer, this may not be the best fit.
faceoff_positive.headline: Need to try , guys

faceoff_negative.comments: Maybelline's Grippy Serum Primer is super hydrating and helps set the perfect foundation for your base. Once applied to the skin this serum primer transforms into an almost sticky finish, this finish helps your base last longer and gives you a nice natural glow, which I loved. I'm a combination skin type and unfortunately, this product did make me more oiler than usual by the end of the day. I had to go a little heavier on the setting powder to control my oil the for the day, which took away from that natural glow that I'm looking to achieve. There was no scent, which I prefer with my face products and I like the dropper - you can really control how much you really want to use. Overall this is a good and affordable primer.
